node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 31, 2021. May be an image of outdoors, brick wall and text that says 'RIGHT PERSON FOR SOMEONE SOMETIMES YOU'LL BE THE WHO IS NOT RIGHT PERSON. READY FOR THE TFW OI AP'.

node.text:
Sometimes you’ll have to let go of what’s not meant for you. You’ll have to accept the truth and know when it’s time to walk away. 

Sometimes you’ll have to redirect all the love you have back to yourself. You’ll have to understand that it’s not always you. Sometimes you’ll learn the hard way, that some people are teaching you how to live yourself by choosing yourself. Sometimes it won’t work out, the more you can accept and be open to discomfort and change the more you’ll see it as an opportunity to grow and heal parts of you that seek out one sided love.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 29, 2021. May be an image of ‎outdoors and ‎text that says '‎AT SOME POINT, YOU'LL HAVE TO REALIZE THAT SOME PEOPLE WON'T BE READY FOR YOUR LOVE. REGENCY بر‎'‎‎.

node.text:
Some people won’t be ready for what you have to offer. Don’t hate them for it. 

Love them through it (at a distance if you need to) people don’t have to choose you, they have to choose themselves first. They have to first believe they are worthy of love. You can spend years chasing, convincing and trying to make someone see your worth. Or you can know it in your heart and be ok with letting them go. Not everyone will be ready for the love you have to give.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 26, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and brick wall.

node.text:
Whatever it is that you’re forcing rn— let it go. 

Good things don’t need to be forced. Things that are meant to be feel happen naturally. Anything that is costing you your peace, excessive effort or too much compromise is telling you something. You won’t have to force what’s meant for you or easily maintained. If you feel like you’re giving way more than you have in order to keep someone’s interest it’s going to cost you later. Let go. Let it be:

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 24, 2021. May be an image of sky, road and text that says 'Don't be surprised when choosing yourself means the end of certain conNec ions.'.

node.text:
Good morning, don’t be surprised. 

Choosing yourself will have consequences. It will end connections you thought would have never ended. That will make you doubt your choice. It will make you question “am I really worth choosing me or am I being extra?” You’re not being extra- choosing yourself will feel mean if you’ve never done it. So will setting boundaries. The more you begin to do this, the more you’ll start to believe in your own worth and attract people who do too.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 21, 2021.

node.text:
There’s a difference between asking for what you need and asking someone who is incapable of meeting your needs. When we ask the wrong person it can become very easy to assume that we are the problem. That we are too “needy“ and this is a major reason why it’s sometimes easier not to speak up or to pretend like you don’t have actual needs. 

Remember that someone who is not emotionally available, someone who isn’t in tune with their own needs, boundaries and emotions is likely not going to be able to understand yours. Let alone meet them. When you ask the wrong person you feel doubt, insecurity unsure of yourself— the best relationships encompass the opposite of that. Security, assurance and love. People who get you and understand you don’t promote those types of feelings. Make sure you’re speaking up for yourself but also make sure you’re not just asking the wrong person.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 18, 2021.

node.text:
Learn to let go of whatever doesn’t want to stay. Learn to not force it. Practice being comfortable with change and being in the unknown. 

Loss isn’t always a loss. Sometimes loss is rebirth, it is a shift into something that is meant to push you out of your comfort zone. Don’t cling to someone or something just because it is familiar, familiar doesn’t always mean healthy. Letting go of people who are ok with losing you is emotionally maturity. It’s self love. It’s saying “I’m sad that they are gone but I’m worthy of people who want to stay.”

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A PERSON CAN HAVE GOOD QUALITIES STILL AND TOXIC BE FOR YOU.'.

node.text:
You’re feelings for them don’t make them perfect and incapable of having flaws. But your feelings for them often tend to make you ignore the parts of them that don’t sit very well with you. 

It’s one thing to be understanding and accepting of peoples shortcomings, but it’s another to continually tolerate and enable them. If you’re not sharing what you need often in fear of seeming like to much or being rejected or abandoned, lean into that fear and face it. Start speaking up and allowing yourself to lose whoever isn’t willing to rise to the standards you want. You are worthy of respect, but you first have to respect yourself.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'YOU ARE ALLOWED TO DISTANCE YOURSELF FROM PEOPLE WHO BEHAVE IN WAYS THAT HURT YOU.'.

node.text:
It’s called boundaries and self respect. It’s called listening to your intuition and setting standards that promote peace of mind. 

When we continually accept or tolerate someone’s disrespectful or hurtful behavior, we are signaling  to our brain that it’s ok and our brain is finding ways to navigate it. You don’t want disrespect to become familiar or the norm. You are right for distancing, and continuing to do so. It’s a strength and a major step in putting yourself first. Don’t be afraid to do that.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 13, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'IT'S NORMAL TO MISS THEM, BUT .UMNT IT MAY HEALTHY NOT REACH OUT. TO'.

node.text:
Brain is constantly looking for ways to feel familiar or comfortable. Process of letting go doesn’t mean you’re no longer going to miss that person, or think about them ever again. Quite the opposite you’re going to ruminate, romanticize, remember the good and it might make you feel like the right thing to do is to engage or reconnect.

Remember that it’s just your brain seeking the familiar, it’s just your brain seeking something that knows how to navigate. It’s just your brain not being comfortable in the unknown, and not being comfortable in change. Remember that before you try to rekindle some thing that you finally had the courage to walk away from.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 11, 2021. May be an image of outdoors, tree and text that says 'Letting People Lose You is a Different Kind of SELF RESPECT'.

node.text:
Letting people lose you is a sign you respect yourself. When you know your worth you are okay with people losing you. You don’t beg anyone to stay or compromise or stay quiet and small to accommodate them. 

When you know your worth you use your voice, you get uncomfortable at times because you set boundaries and assert your needs. When you know your worth mistreatment and disrespect is no longer tolerable. The biggest sign that you respect yourself is being okay with losing anyone who no longer mirrors your values. When you know your worth you don’t force or struggle to feel heard and seen because you understand that anyone who loses you isn’t meant to stay.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 10, 2021. May be an image of sky and text that says 'MAKE SURE YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE WHO ACTUALLY VALUES THE CONNECTION. S 0546'.

node.text:
Make sure there is reciprocity. Make sure there is respect of boundaries. Make sure there is a matched effort. Make sure you’re not the only one being vulnerable or acting like the connection matters. Make sure it’s not one sided. Make sure you’re not the only on working to make it work, no real connection will have to be forced. 

Make sure you’re aware of what you need in order to feel safe in the connection. Make sure you communicate that, make sure you feel safe to communicate and share who you are. Make sure you’re not devaluing yourself to stay in something that is lowering contributing to a low self esteem.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by THE FEMALE on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'ATTACHMENT SOMEONE TOOK LOSING YOU WHO TO FOR HITS GRANTED DIFFERENT'.

node.text:
It hits different when you stop pursuing relationships that are one sided. It hits different when you set some boundaries and watch people who benefiting from you having none, fall by the wayside. 

It hits different when you start to practice self love and no longer engage with people who don’t value and support you. When you start believing your worth and understand that connections that leave you anxious, stressed or doubtful are only signals that they’re not for you. All of this is hard work and it’s not easy but when you begin making choices that support who you want to become rather that what’s familiar, a lot of things will start to change.
